column5: Well good morning from the north.Like this temperature in the summer but not in winter.
Feels like -32, but actually warmer, eh? Bill
If you decide to go outside, make sure to wear some sunscreen. I see a little sun poking out from behind that cloud.
-23 here in International Falls when I got moving this morning. Not a Mosquito in sight.
A balmy 20 here this morning John.... been a strange winter. Haven't had any ice to get out on yet... maybe this week.
Well I went out to load my stove up and really didn't feel any warmer.
Think you would have ice at 20f
Much less snow so far this year than last up there? Long way to go but wonder what water levels will be like by the time late May rolls aroundâ€¦.

We do have quite a bit of snow really.My snow banks from plowing are pretty normal looking.Water levels were low in the fall as usuall and will get some spring melt to bring it up.Definately not going to be like last year.
